BFN 

<F P=106> [By Sofia Wu] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, April 26 (CNA) -- Shih Ke-min, deputy 
director of the Cultural Affairs Department of the ruling 
Kuomintang [KMT], has been named the next president of the 
CENTRAL NEWS AGENCY [CNA]. 
  Shih, 58, will succeed P.P. Tang, who will become president 
of the KMT-run CENTRAL DAILY NEWS. 
  An experienced journalist, Shih joined the Tainan-based 
CHINA 
DAILY NEWS shortly after he graduated from National Taiwan 
Normal University. He later became a UNITED DAILY NEWS 
correspondent and bureau chief in Washington, D.C. 
  He returned to Taipei last May to assume the KMT post after 
living in the U.S. for 25 years. 
  He will assume his new post after a ceremony to be held 
sometime next month. 

